        Select distinct column.

        @NonNull
 @CheckResult
public static <P,X extends NumericColumn<?,?,? extends java.lang.Number,P>> NumericColumn<java.lang.Double,java.lang.Double,java.lang.Number,P> avg(@NonNull
                                                                                                                                                                           X column)

        The avg() function returns the average value of all non-NULL X within a group. String and BLOB values that do not look like numbers are interpreted as 0.

        The result of avg() is always a floating point value as long as at there is at least one non-NULL input even if all inputs are integers. The result of avg() is NULL if and only if there are no non-NULL inputs.

        column - Input of this aggregate function

      • sum

 @CheckResult

                                                                                                                                                                           X column)

        Sum function that uses internally total() SQLite aggregate function.

        The function returns sum of all non-NULL values in the group. If there are no non-NULL input rows then function returns 0.0. The result of function is always a floating point value. This function never throws an integer overflow.

                                                                                                                                       X column)
        The abs(X) function returns the absolute value of the numeric argument X. Abs(X) returns NULL if X is NULL. If X is the integer -9223372036854775808 then abs(X) throws an integer overflow error since there is no equivalent positive 64-bit two complement value.

      • length

        @NonNull
 @CheckResult
public static <P,X extends Column<?,?,?,P>> NumericColumn<java.lang.Long,java.lang.Long,java.lang.Number,P> length(@NonNull
                                                                                                                                          X column)
        For a string value X, the length(X) function returns the number of characters (not bytes) in X prior to the first NUL character. Since SQLite strings do not normally contain NUL characters, the length(X) function will usually return the total number of characters in the string X. For a blob value X, length(X) returns the number of bytes in the blob. If X is NULL then length(X) is NULL. If X is numeric then length(X) returns the length of a string representation of X.
        Parameters:
        column - Input of this function
        Returns:
        Column representing the result of this function
        See Also:
        SQLite documentation: Core Functions
